article.headline: NEW YORK 93, HOUSTON 92
article.story:
HOUSTON (Ticker) -- Tracy McGrady gave Jamal Crawford and the 
New York Knicks too much time.

Crawford, who scored 19 points, banked in a 3-pointer at the
buzzer as the Knicks rallied from an 11-point fourth-quarter
deficit to stun the Houston Rockets, 93-92.

Houston held a 92-88 lead before Knicks forward Kurt Thomas
nailed a jumper with 26.8 seconds remaining.  New York elected
not to foul, but McGrady did not run down all of the shot clock
before missing a floater in the lane with four seconds left.

Thomas grabbed the rebound with 2.9 seconds to go and the Knicks
called a timeout to set up a final play.  Crawford got the
inbounds pass near the top of the arc, dribbled to his right and
cleanly got off a shot over Houston swingman Jim Jackson.  The
ball bounced off the backboard and swished through the net,
stunning the Rockets and the Toyota Center crowd.

Thomas collected 23 points and 14 rebounds and Stephon Marbury
added 18 and 10 assists for New York, which improved to 1-2
against Houston since former Knicks coach Jeff Van Gundy took
over the Rockets prior to last season.

The Knicks trailed by as many as 12 points in the third quarter
and 72-61 entering the fourth before opening the period with an
11-0 run.  Houston opened a 90-85 advantage on a 3-pointer by
Tyronn Lue with 2:13 left, but Thomas scored five points down
the stretch to set up Crawford's heroics.

McGrady contributed 24 points and eight assists and Yao Ming
chipped in 23 and 11 rebounds for Houston, which slipped to 1-4
against Eastern Conference opponents.
